						<div class="postbody">Nowadays people put controller reads immediately after sprite DMA in order to prevent a glitch related to DPCM sounds. See: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Controller_Reading#DPCM_Safety_using_OAM_DMA">https://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Con ... ng_OAM_DMA</a><!-- m --><br /><br />You don't have to understand what those words mean in order to use it. Just copy/paste the code from the wiki into your NMI subroutine.</div>

